            "text": "I printed a year's daily writing, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/KenSmith/status/1567950123283451906\">a few hundred blog posts</a>, and slipped the pages into two spring-back binders, which are designed for manuscripts in process. You can write in the margins, and later, if you revise the digital file, you can print a new copy of the page and exchange it for the old one in a few seconds. It's like a book where you can move the pages around any time you want, or add and subtract pages. Groovy poets used to shape book manuscripts in these binders, once upon a time.",
