{
    "text": "Pure and impure information",
    "created": "Thu, 08 Sep 2022 23:54:29 GMT",
    "type": "outline",
    "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/09/08/235429.html?title=pureAndImpureInformation",
    "subs": [
        {
            "text": "I imagine that there are <i>two kinds of information, pure and impure</i>.",
            "created": "Thu, 08 Sep 2022 23:54:33 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/09/08/235429.html?title=pureAndImpureInformation#a235433"
        },
        {
            "text": "Pure information is produced by experts, using their refined procedures, and certified as pure by other experts. It's structure derives from the concepts of the field, which are visible very near the surface of the information. Pure information belongs to the experts that produce it and the corporations and governments that hire them for certain projects.",
            "created": "Thu, 08 Sep 2022 23:59:49 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/09/08/235429.html?title=pureAndImpureInformation#a235949"
        },
        {
            "text": "Impure information is produced by experts, witnesses, hobbyists, whoever, and it is made impure by contact with people attempting to test and use the information for great or small purposes in the practical world. All the contact scratches and stretches and strains the pure information, and other bits of lore and information adhere to the surface until the structure is no longer clear and pure. Some people get very good at using impure information to get things done, and impure information can improve over time, with use and reflection. Impure information belongs to the people that use it and that hand it down to others.",
            "created": "Fri, 09 Sep 2022 00:00:31 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/09/08/235429.html?title=pureAndImpureInformation#a000031"
        },
        {
            "text": "Schools never teach about the existence of these two kinds of information, and often schools try to rid the scene of impure information anyway. Schools tend to like social systems that honor the experts who produce pure information, and schools often look upon the masters of impure information as renegades. [See 12/21/21 post.]",
            "created": "Fri, 09 Sep 2022 00:07:07 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/09/08/235429.html?title=pureAndImpureInformation#a000707"
        }
    ]
}

